			<ns0:name>vi...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/103223416233877126719/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We are going to implement interception of berkeley sockets system calls (primarily for nacl-mounts), so that it would be possible to port networking apps to Native Client. This target is glibc-only, Newlib does not contain necessary headers.

&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
There's an implementation of sockets for Native Client by Dmitry Polukhin in his famous NaCl SSH client; glibc changes (http://git.chromium.org/gitweb/?p=native_client/nacl-glibc.git;a=commit;h=1de757e49cb7f3bb6708be56a8ef6f3a749e1252) are propagated to SDK now, so main target today is nacl-mounts implementation.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
NaCl SSH re-built using nacl-ports sockets implementation.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
Ability to port a wide range of networking apps.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-05-04T15:27:08.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-05-03T12:37:29.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Started</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
